    "how_to_grow": {
        "cultivation": {
            "text": "Place tubers, hollow-side up, on top of well-drained soil in shallow containers in a light potting mix around 2-4\" apart, handling tubers with care as they are very fragile. Place in a bright location, away from direct sunlight. Tubers should show growth between 2 and 6 weeks after planting. Tubers can be transplanted after the first 2 leaves have grown and planted out with the risk of frost has passed. Plants can be overwintered then re-planted the following spring. See begonias: outdoors for further advice",
